.TH "hid_hw_start" 9 "hid_hw_start" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hid_hw_start \- start underlying HW
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hid_hw_start
.BI "(struct hid_device *hdev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int connect_mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hdev" 12
hid device
.IP "connect_mask" 12
which outputs to connect, see HID_CONNECT_*
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Call this in probe function *after* hid_parse. This will setup HW
buffers and start the device (if not defeirred to device open).
hid_hw_stop must be called if this was successful.
